prevention of crime and disorder</li>\n  <li>the prevention of public nuisance</li>\n  <li>the protection of children from harm</li>\n  <li>public safety</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Your request might be rejected if it’s trivial, is about an issue that’s been considered before or doesn’t relate to one of the above.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>To ask for a review, write to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the licensing authority (local council)</li>\n  <li>the licence holder</li>\n  <li>the &lsquo;responsible authorities&rsquo; (details and addresses will be available from the licensing authority) </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If your request for a review is accepted, the licensing authority will advertise this and ask for comments - people have 28 days to give them.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also be invited to the review hearing, where you can speak if you want to. </p>\n\n<h2>Decisions the licensing authority can make</h2>\n\n<p>After the hearing, the licensing authority might:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>take no action</li>\n  <li>change, add or remove licence conditions</li>\n  <li>exclude certain activities from the licence</li>\n  <li>remove the &lsquo;premises supervisor&rsquo; (the person named in the licence who controls the premises)</li>\n  <li>suspend the licence for up to 3 months</li>\n  <li>revoke the licence</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Anyone involved in a licence review can appeal the licensing authority&rsquo;s decision to the magistrates&rsquo; court.</p>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Safety and the environment in your community","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/housing%2Fsafety-environment.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes waste, rubbish and recycling, noise pollution and local emergencies","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=housing%2Fsafety-environment","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/housing/safety-environment"},"parent":{"title":"Housing and lo