 money</a> in instalments through your electricity bill</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You can get an assessment now, but work can’t start until 28 January 2013.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you’re a landlord, you must get your tenant’s permission before you sign up, and if you’re a tenant you must get your landlord’s permission to sign up - this also applies to social housing.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>More information</h2>\n\n<p>Get more information about the Green Deal.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Energy Saving Advice Service</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>0300 123 1234<br />\nMonday to Friday, 9am to 8pm<br />\nSaturday, 10am to 2pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Energy Saving Scotland</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>0800 512 012<br />\nMonday to Friday, 9am to 5pm</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/green-deal-energy-saving-measures/getting-an-assessment","slug":"getting-an-assessment","order":2,"title":"Getting an assessment","body":"<p>You&rsquo;ll need to choose an authorised <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.greendealorb.co.uk/assessors/assessor-search\" title=\"Find a Green Deal assessor\">Green Deal assessor.</a> They will visit your home, talk to you about your property and your energy use and tell you whether you could benefit from Green Deal improvements. </p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll be given a Green Deal Advice Report - this will explain what improvements you can make and estimate how much you could save on your energy bills.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You may have to pay for an assessment - you should check with the assessor before the appointment.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If the assessor intends to quote for improvements, or recommend specific products or providers, they&rsquo;ll need your permission before they do the assessment. </p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://assets.digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk/static/green_deal_quality_mark.